						<div class="postbody">I thought you guys might like this video: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=784MUbDoLjQ">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=784MUbDoLjQ</a><!-- m --> I've seen all of these ports, but this is the first time I have ever heard a technical explanation of any of them. I find it funny how shitty Doom ran on what were supposed to be the &quot;top-of the-line&quot; video game systems of the era, even if it was due to software rendering. I've never quite realized how much more powerful the N64's CPU is over the PS1's and Saturn's if it can software render Doom with seemingly perfect performance at 320x200 (<!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6EPKKaZ3Z0A">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6EPKKaZ3Z0A</a><!-- m -->), although it is made with hardware two years more advanced. Two years seemed to be a lot back then for computer hardware, as I don't think you could even run Doom at full settings and 35fps with a computer from a date earlier than 1991. I wasn't even alive during this time though, so what do I know. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_lol.gif" alt=":lol:" title="Laughing" /></div>

